-- BMW Considers Sedan Version of Mini, FT Deutschland Reports
-- B y   C h r i s   R e i t e r
-- 2012-01-23T08:01:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/bmw-considers-sedan-version-of-mini-ft-deutschland-reports.html
Bayerische Motoren Werke AG is
considering a sedan version of its Mini brand, as part of an
expansion of its lineup, the  Financial Times Deutschland 
reported, without citing the source of the information.  The Mini may be expanded to as many as 10 variants from
six, the newspaper reported, citing brand chief Kay Segler. Mini
plans to expand sales to 300,000 by 2013, from 285,060 last
year, the FT Deutschland said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Reiter in Berlin at 
 creiter2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chad Thomas at 
 cthomas16@bloomberg.net  